.SH "NAME"
skb_pad \- zero pad the tail of an skb
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ skb_pad('u
.BI "int skb_pad(struct\ sk_buff\ *\ " "skb" ", int\ " "pad" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIskb\fR
.RS 4
buffer to pad
.RE
.PP
\fIpad\fR
.RS 4
space to pad
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Ensure that a buffer is followed by a padding area that is zero filled\&. Used by network drivers which may DMA or transfer data beyond the buffer end onto the wire\&.
.PP
May return error in out of memory cases\&. The skb is freed on error\&.
